    <stitle>CE 200 AND CE 300 BUS BODY COMPONENTS - Description - Front End</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Front End</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The front end components are listed in more descriptive detail in the Hood, Fender and Grille Service
                Manual. Refer to S09009 for detail instructions for serviceability of the various front end components.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Crossing Control Gate</title>
            <para>The Crossing Control gate (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700406">Figure 6 Item 1</hotlnk>) is a standard component on the CE Series bus. The
                gate is activated by the door opening mechanism and bus warning lights.
            </para>
            <figure id="f4700406" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Crossing Control Gate and Front Bumper</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CROSSING CONTROL GATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRONT BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cross View Mirrors</title>
            <para>The Cross View Mirrors are also a standard feature on the CE Series school bus. These mirrors allow
                cross frontal views of the students' activity at the front and sides of the bus entrance.
            </para>
            <figure id="f4700407" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700407.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Cross View Mirrors</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TYPICAL CROSS VIEW MIRROR ASSEMBLIES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood and Related Components</title>
            <para>The hood and related components are more specifically described in the Hood, Fender and Grille Service
                Manual (S09009). The front end components are designed to enhance the overall safety and functionality
                of the entire school bus.
            </para>
            <figure id="f4700408" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700408.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Front End</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FRONT HOOD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PASSENGER SIDE EXTERIOR MOUNTED REAR VIEW MIRROR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SCHOOL BUS FRONT WARNING LIGHTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRONT SCHOOL BUS IDENTIFICATION PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. DRIVERS SIDE EXTERIOR MOUNTED REAR VIEW MIRROR</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. ENGINE AIR INLET ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. FRONT FENDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. FRONT WHEEL MUD FLAPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. HEADLIGHT AND DIRECTIONAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. GRILLE AND SHROUD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. FRONT BUMPER ASSEMBLY WITH SAFETY GATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. SAFETY GATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. CROSS VIEW MIRRORS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
